; {{ill|Makimuku Katsuyama Kofun|ja|纒向勝山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} : Artifacts from the surrounding moat include wooden sword hilts, ritual fans, and Makimuku-period pottery. The layout forms an equilateral triangle with the Ishizuka and Yazuka mounds.
; {{ill|Higaida Otsuka Kofun|ja|東田大塚古墳|1=Higaida Ōtsuka Kofun|lt=Higaida Ōtsuka Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} : Located in Higashida, Sakurai City. Artifacts include pottery and wooden items. Excavations suggest the presence of jar coffins along the outer embankment.
; {{ill|Hokenoyama Kofun|ja|ホケノ山古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} : A wooden cist burial chamber was found containing a cypress boat-shaped coffin. Artifacts include bronze arrowheads, swords, and mirrors.<ref>{{harvnb|Kashihara Archaeological Institute|2008}}</ref>
